defaultAll consumers should be able to open a bank account unless they have a
default 
defaultcriminal conviction
default that prevents them from doing s
defaulto.
default• Branches should have opening hours to suit consumers and provide a full
default 
defaultrange of services.
default• Staff should be involved in training programmes to deal with every
default 
defaulteventuality and 
defaultbe empowered to make decisions to help consumers quickly.
default• Fees and charges should be transparent, fair and proportionate.
default• Better communication around how consumers are protected online and training to use these services are vital.
default• Contacting the bank should cost the same for new and existing
default 
defaultcustomers. More detail is needed on how much it costs to call using
default 
defaultdifferent networks.
default• Communications should be in plain English. More work is needed to 
defaultrevise how 
defaultchanges to products can be more easily communicated whilst remaining within the guidelines from the financial regulator.
default• Product offerings should be presented in a way that helps consumers compare the full range of services and know that they can switch.
default• The complaints process should be available from all points of contact,
default 
defaultverbal 
defaultcomplaints logged and actioned and leaflets available in branch displays.
default• A review of packaged accounts, eligibility processes and usage of
default 
defaultindividual 
defaultservices is needed.
