defaultPreviously the Financial Services Authority (FSA) supervision policy allowed for increased scrutiny of the largest firms with the largest number of customers across the UK. 
defaultThis meant that not all banks operating in NI were receiving the same robust and persistent supervision.   We are expecting to see a more detailed level of testing extended to NI now that FCA has taken up its new role.
